Patch Set 18:

(2 comments)

This commit message could be improved.  It's not clear to me why adding coroutines, detecting size changes of nbd devices, or calling associated callbacks are useful to virtual media.  Considering we're still not to the point where we can actually mount an nbd device, I'm not really sure why these are useful.
What does this mean?  How did you test this?
